The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Alert for Calcutta
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Alert for Calcutta
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                               
	New Delhi, March 8: The Centre today issued alerts on possible terror strikes by Indian Mujahideen (IM) militants in Calcutta, Mumbai and Bangalore.        
	The Union home ministry has sent terror alerts to the governments of Bengal, Karnataka and Maharashtra. A home ministry official claimed that the alerts were based on information gleaned from recently arrested alleged IM operatives.        
	We are not taking any chances on whatever information we have received. So, we have alerted the state governments concerned to take all necessary security measures immediately, a home ministry official said.        
	The alerts were issued after the interrogation of Salman, a suspect in the serial blasts in Ahmedabad, Varanasi and Gorakhpur and two other alleged IM militants, hailing from Uttar Pradesh but arrested from the Indo-Bangladesh border. Sources said more arrests would take place in the coming days.        
	Govt Maoist claim        
	The Union home ministry has claimed that an increasing number of Maoists have become deeply disenchanted with their own cadres extortion and their harassment of the poor and marked departure from ideology.        
	The ministry said three Maoists who surrendered in Orissas Kandhamal last month had talked about their disillusionment with the CPI (Maoist) after witnessing cadres indulging in extortion.                                                                                                                                                          
